              <p align="left" class="style2"><strong><a href="http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2005-05/14/content_2956557.htm">Nation strives for more say in technical standards</a><br>
                </strong><strong>By:</strong> Zhao Xiaohui <br>
                <strong>China View, Beijing, May 14, 2005 --</strong> After paying &quot;patent rent&quot; for many years, Chinese high-tech companies are faced with more and more intellectual property rights disputes and trade barriers. It has become an urgent task for China to strive for more say in making technical standards. &quot;The formation of technical standard has shifted from 'marketdecides standards' in the past to today's 'standards lead markets',&quot; said Zhang Qin, deputy director of the State Intellectual Property Office. ...<a href="http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2005-05/14/content_2956557.htm">Full Story</a></p>
